The U.S. government placed eight more Chinese companies including drone manufacturer DJI on an investment blocklist after imposing investment restrictions on SenseTime, resorting to a de facto "decoupling". It is extremely irresponsible if in the end the U.S. side forces global capital reallocate based on its biased policies, which will impede global economic growth. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Kate Kui explains.